---
// input: siteConfig data, related guides list layout component
// output: Progression guide page outlining cash acceleration and board slot speedrun
// pos: src/pages/progression.astro (更新规则：文件变更需同步本注释与所属目录 README)

import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import RelatedGuides from "../components/RelatedGuides.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../data/config";
---

<SiteLayout title="Merge a Nuke Guide Progression | Roblox Cash Speedrun" description="Follow the official Merge a Nuke guide progression path to build cash. Learn advanced merging slots order, multipliers investment, and tycoon expansion.">
  <main class="content-page">
    <section class="prose-block" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Progression</p>
      <h1>{siteConfig.gameName} Progression Guide</h1>
      <p>Accelerating your progression rate is the ultimate test of economic management inside Roblox Merge a Nuke Tycoon. This page outlines the step-by-step roadmap to turn early-game code rewards into late-game rebirth multipliers without wasting cash.</p>
      
      <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 20px; background: rgba(30, 144, 255, 0.05); border: 1.5px solid rgba(30, 144, 255, 0.15); border-radius: var(--radius-interactive); line-height: 1.6;">
        <h3 style="color: var(--color-blue); margin-bottom: 8px;">Progression Strategy Rationale</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          To build a dominant atomic base, players must avoid early-game pitfalls. Many beginners rush into active PVP combat without securing passive income. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> focus is to help you maintain a clean board, focus on spawn-rate upgrades, and transition smoothly into highly lucrative rebirth cycles.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Video Guide: Fastest Progression Path</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.6;">Want to see a visual step-by-step walkthrough of the fastest way to progress, buy base expansions, and trigger rebirths? Watch the video below to master the gameplay route.</p>
      <div style="margin: 24px 0; max-width: 800px; aspect-ratio: 16/9; width: 100%;">
        <iframe 
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/KG_lFaKZW1o" 
          title="Merge a Nuke Tycoon Progression Walkthrough" 
          frameborder="0" 
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" 
          allowfullscreen
          style="width: 100%; height: 100%; border-radius: var(--radius-card); border: 1px solid var(--line);"
        ></iframe>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="cash-engine" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Cash engine</p>
      <h2 id="cash-engine" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Build your tycoon cash engine</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 1.6;">Your primary goal is to maximize the cash-per-minute rate generated by the active nukes sitting in your base hangar. Spending too much currency on early raid items slows down your overall merge velocity. Reinvesting local earnings back into the tycoon's core attributes is the most efficient path forward.</p>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--color-yellow); margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.1rem; font-family: var(--font-display);">Optimizing board real estate</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Maintaining open slots on your island grid is vital for progression. When you spawn lower-tier bombs too quickly, they clog the workspace. This prevents you from executing matching combinations. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> recommends keeping at least 30% of your board completely open at all times to allow for smooth merge chains.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">If your board becomes overcrowded, do not buy more spawns. Focus on clearing out duplicate lowest-tier bombs. Grouping similar bomb tiers in distinct quadrants also makes matching faster, reducing early-game friction and keeping your progression speed high.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--color-yellow); margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.1rem; font-family: var(--font-display);">Prioritizing multiplier purchases</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Cash multipliers determine how much passive currency you receive per second. Instead of hoarding game cash, spend it immediately on incubator and spawn upgrades. The faster you can spawn tier-2 or tier-3 missiles, the fewer merges you need to perform to unlock high-tier assets.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">According to community data analyzed for this <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong>, upgrading spawn level tier capacity offers the highest economic return. Focus on building a stable foundation before investing cash in base locks, nuke health upgrades, or PvP raid cooldown reduction perks.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section grid-section" aria-labelledby="speedrun-strategy" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Speedrun</p>
        <h2 id="speedrun-strategy">Late game merging speedrun</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Handling exponential cost scaling</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">As you climb weapon tiers, the merge requirement increases exponentially. Spawning a high-level nuclear warhead requires hundreds of tier-1 merges. To counter this scaling lag, players must unlock base rebirth features as quickly as possible.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> advises against trying to reach max-tier missiles during your first rebirth cycle. Focus on hitting the minimum cash required to trigger a rebirth. The permanent multiplier boost will make subsequent merging runs significantly faster and less tedious.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Rebirthing resets active cash but permanent boosts make early-tier merging instantly trivial.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Reinvesting offline profits</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Offline cash accumulation is a powerful feature for players who cannot play constantly. However, the offline engine is only useful if your board is set up correctly before logging out. Always place your highest-tier active weapons in the hangar slots to maximize yield.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">When returning to the server, instantly spend your accumulated offline cash on spawning level upgrades. By following this <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> reinvestment loop, you compound your cash gains, accelerating progression and ensuring your base reaches top-tier status rapidly.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Compounds offline profits immediately upon logging in to maximize your tycoon growth rate.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="section faq-block" style="margin-bottom: 48px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); padding-top: 40px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 32px; color: var(--color-yellow); font-family: var(--font-display);">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div style="display: grid; gap: 24px;">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. How do I speed up my Merge a Nuke progression?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. To progress as fast as possible, redeem the active code multipliers first, upgrade your **Spawn Tier** to skip low-level merges, and perform a **Rebirth** the moment upgrades start feeling expensive. The permanent multiplier boost resets the grind.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. How many open grid slots should I keep?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. We recommend keeping at least <strong>30% of your board slots completely open</strong>. If your grid fills up with low-tier duplicates, you won't have enough room to cycle through spawn sequences, which temporarily stalls your matching progress.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line); padding: 24px;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: var(--font-display);">Q. Is active merging faster than idle offline cash?</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text);">
            A. Active merging is much faster in the early stages, as you actively clear slots and combine weapons. However, late-game builds heavily rely on offline passive income, boosted by Rebirth multipliers, to accumulate millions of dollars overnight.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <RelatedGuides currentSlug="progression" />
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
